I could live like this forever, she thought naively. Right here on this
beach.
And then, one day, Anthony disappeared.
When she thought to look him up years later, she had discovered that
he’d had a heart-attack. Only thirty-two. What a fucking waste. You really
couldn’t depend on anyone other than yourself. They’d always leave you,
one way or another. Her mouth twisted bitterly.
Even your own children could turn traitor.
She looked a lot like him in certain lights—the ringlets in her curly
hair, the sharp jut of her slightly crooked nose, and the way her forehead
wrinkled when she frowned. That was all him. But it was in the face, too.
Anthony’s face had been incredibly expressive and she had loved that about
