“It’s still dark out, you monster.”
“So it’s only Daddy you won’t play nice with.”
“Fuck you, Nicholas.”
“If we didn’t have a plane to catch,” he said, “I would.”
Jay set her teeth. The U-Haul driver Nicholas had hired had left with
her things very early in the morning, and he had booked a red-eye flight
