“You were like a dreamer living in a fairytale. You thought there was
goodness in restraint. But there isn’t.” He straightened, the fabric of his
jacket rippling. “When you feed your dreams to the bonfire, you just end up
with a pile of cold dead ashes and a whole lot of nothing.”
Jay laughed humorlessly. “Says the boy who thinks he can buy his way
out of trouble with a fistful of twenties.”
“Oh, blue jay. Don’t tell me you dragged me out here just to be sad.”
She shivered again and he shrugged out of his dinner jacket. It was the one
