Austen’s collected works, clearly well-loved, and her heart sank a little at
the thought of a woman who had yearned for that kind of romance, only to
find herself married to a man like Damon.
In a silver frame, she found a picture of the woman whose ghost she
had glimpsed in the features of her son. Emma Beaucroft was more striking
than pretty, with sharp cheekbones and brows that looked like brushstrokes.
Her hair was cut fashionably short but quite wavy, and Jay, with a tight
chest, recognized that same curl pattern from Nicholas, when his hair was
wet.
