was very snug, and her ass and bust stretched the fabric to its limit, but it fit,
and she knew Nicholas would like the low decolletage.
She thought of that nightmare when she’d been wearing her mother’s
Vegas wedding dress. This was the class her mother had always tried to
emulate. Jay smoothed her hands over her own hips before looking away
from her own reflection.
Stepping into this dress, and into this life, made it feel an awful lot like
she was taking her mother’s place, along with his name.
I’ll be the third Mrs. Beaucroft to live in this house.
Jay set the photo and the book on the coffee table of Nicholas’s
