you were trying to do, but beating up my ex-boyfriend isn’t going to unprint what that stupid newspaper said about us.”
“Are you sure it didn’t turn your crank at least a little, seeing me mop
the floor with that waste?” Another harsh breath escaped him as she wound
the bandage around his hand. He flexed his knuckles. “I thought you liked it
when Daddy got mean.”
“Cut it out,” she said, in a missish voice that had him stirring. “You
could have gone to jail. Or worse. Don’t shake your head at me,” she
snapped, furious again, seeing the smirk tugging at his lips. “Even you’re
not above the law, despite what you seem to think. Did you really think he
took those pictures? Hand to heart.”
No,” he admitted. “But whoever did it knew their way around our
house so it could have been him, and to be honest, after you told me what
he said to you, I wanted to put a little fear of god into him, anyway.” He let
his hands fall to his sides, tilting his head obediently when she leaned in to
