“Jake Van Hoff? Your friend from school?”
“We’re not friends,” he reminded her. “But yes. Him.”
“Why?”
“Because he’s your mother’s little boy toy.”
She let out a disbelieving laugh as she twisted to toss the bloodied Qtip in her hand in the trash. “He’s not exactly her type.”
“He’s got a cock and a pulse. Of course he’s her type. He also has
something she wants; he works for his uncle.” He took the bottle of alcohol
from her loosened grip, screwing the cap on tightly and setting it on the
