Nicholas eyed her. “Do I look like one of your girlfriends?”
Jay saw her mother’s mouth open, ready to deliver a cutting remark.
Then she appeared to think better of it. “Your father never said no.”
Nicholas just looked at her. She swallowed, and then covered her
unease with a shrug.
“Justine, wine?” It sounded like a command.
“Fine.” She didn’t want it, either, but it would give her something to do
with her hands, which were shaking quite badly. Nicholas raised a
