She sounded as if being eighteen were a crime, Jay thought. Perhaps, to
a woman like her mother, it was. The sour tang of bile rose in her throat.
“That’s a fucking lie. He tried to—”
But she couldn’t finish. All she could taste was that cheap acidic wine.
He wanted to own me.
“You see? You can’t even deny it. Just like this thing you have with
