Jay woke up to the smell of smoke.
She shot out of bed, panicked to find herself alone, the sheets next to
her cold. But then she went to the window and looked through the glass, her
breath fogging the clear surface.
Nicholas had the fire pit lit. The orange glow of the flames softened his
